At least two taxi passengers have died on Wednesday morning on the N3 southbound carriageway near Ashburton outside Pietermaritzburg. Sources at the scene said the accident happened when a container fell off a truck and landed on the taxi. Twelve people have been injured, with some of them in a serious condition. The taxi was pushed up against the guard rail and emergency workers were searching the wreckage and nearby veld for more injured people. The taxi is believed to be from Gauteng. The crash occurred in the dip in the road before the Ashburton bridge.  Robert MacKenzie from KZN EMS said paramedics have treated 12 patients, four seriously injured and eight with minor injuries. The highway is closed as emergency services work to clear the scene.